Reading through various comments and quote tweets I don't think people realize why the price is the way it is.

Genesis used to be just Friday and Saturday. Sunday has been added to make it a 3-day event

Genesis used to charge for Top 8 passes. Those are included now

To update this, Genesis 9 is not a good comparison because Top 8 was in the convention center. Even with that it was still $99 for early bird.

Looking at Genesis 8, Early Bird was $75, Top 8 was $35. You were paying $110 for early bird before, and you get an entire extra day now

Compare these prices to other larger events like Evo. The prices are similar. This is just what it costs to put on a show as big as this in places like California now!

Combine that with stripe banning esports events from their payment processing. We'll see more of this in 2024
